data.nav:
data/startpage.swf
fully XML driven; very simple XML;
multilingual - ready for any language (chinese, japanese, arabic, russian etc.), including combinations of two or more languages; just fill the text in XML;
replaceable video background - external FLV video, easily replaceable, just copy and paste;
HTML formatted text support - the use of CDATA is not necessary; just write the HTML tags in XML directly;
the template is extendable via the XML by loading external SWF files (with control over the ambient music); an example is the HOME page of the preview;
PayPal Buy option for the items presented in the galleries;
menus based navigations with unlimited levels of submenus - no setup/coding necessary, just define the items in XML;
news presentation;
team members presentation;
menus and buttons customization details in the User Guide;
powerful multimedia galleries;
info mini galleries (image and text, side by side);
ambient music playlist (XML) and control;
free to place the external SWF pages, external links, content (html text) pages, galleries, news, team-members anywhere among the menu/submenus' items and to use them repeatedly;
replaceable external SWF+PHP contact form;
external logo (GIF, JPG, PNG, SWF) loaded via XML;
lightweight file: the declared size of 128kb includes all mentioned capabilities and all players.
direct YouTube media stream (normal and high quality) with full user control; requires PHP support on server;
GIF/JPG/PNG images presentation with scaling and zoom control;
SWF Flash animations with full control;
FLV-H.264 videos presentation with full control;
MP3 audios presentation with full control, customizable (XML) Real Time Spectrum Analyzer and customizable (XML) slow-motion video effect;
the previously enumerated media types can be added all together to a gallery;
gallery auto-play (slide-show) with play/pause control;
ambient music automatic fade-out/fade-in when a video, an audio or a swf starts/ends;
no need to create thumbnails for the items added to the galleries - the template implements an advanced Automatic Thumbnails Generator (ATG). This means it is not necessary to provide thumbnails for the images, videos or audios you add to a gallery – in case of images, the ATG mechanism will silently download in the “background” the image itself WHEN the bandwidth is not used (the download is suspended when a multimedia file is loaded and resumed when the loading process ends) and the result (bitmap data) will be resized (in order to save memory resources) and used as thumbnail (the thumbnails dimensions are defined in the data.xml file); in case of audios, videos and YouTube streamed materials default thumbnails are provided; positive side effects: the gallery loads instantly; the loaded images remain in cache (on the website visitor’s computer) and are immediately available when necessary; in addition, you had the possibility to indicate a specific thumbnail to be displayed in case of a gallery item.
You are able to extend your website capabilities by loading standalone external SWF files (simply by indicating the URL/path to that external SWF file in the XML file). The User Guide includes details and a practical example about how to do this.
The template is ready for direct use - default values are provided. Though, you had the possibility to modify the default setup by altering the parameters in the XML file - some of the parameters which are available for changes:
the video background URL/path;
the video background scale mode (preserving or not the aspect ratio);
the ambient music initial auto-start or not;
the ambient music initial volume;
the ambient music playlist (the URLs/paths to the MP3 files);
the MP3 audio stream buffer length;
the video stream buffer length;
the multimedia galleries auto-play timer;
the multimedia galleries initial sound volume;
the Real Time Spectrum Analyzer color presets for bands and peak levels;
the multimedia, mini, news and team-members galleries thumbnails dimensions - height and width;
media watermarks (video, YouTube normal/high quality);
the mode the external links will open: in a new window/tab or in the same window
the contact form URL/path (in case you want to use a different contact form than the one provided by this template);
the text placed in header (usually copyright info); the text is HTML formatted - links are available too;
your logo external file (GIF/JPG/PNG/SWF) URL/path;
the PayPal configuration (if you want to sell items via PayPal): your bussiness e-mail address, PayPal currency (USD by default), location (US by default), your shopping cart site, item ID and PRICE (if you want to be displayed in a language other than english);
change the video background by replacing it with a different one - just copy and paste the new video background (and update the XML with the new URL/path if the new video file has a different name and/or is located elsewhere); this simple operation will have a major impact over your website general look and feel;
change the main decoration element - the red line; this is an unique movie clip in the FLA file library (details in the User Guide on how to retrieve this movie clip in the library); once this movie clip changes (animation, colors...) you'll see the results in your entire website;
change the interface controls - buttons, menus, highlight bars etc. aspect; these controls are all movie clips in the FLA file library and you are free to customize them (animations, colors...); the User Guide provides details on how to retrieve these movie clips in the library;
change the text styles (colors, font size, font weight etc.) for all the text displaying units of the template in the CSS manner (details provided in the User Guide)
change the left side images display style for the team-members and mini-galleries in the XML directly: choose a rectangular or a styled contour - you are able to modify the styled contour by editing the FLA file
Dynamic content with HTML formatted text
All supported HTML tags are available - no need to use CDATA. Links, lists, GIF, JPG or PNG images, SWF Flash animations, bold, italic, underlined text etc. can be inserted using standard HTML tags.
A set of basic predefined styles is allready built in; all these styles can be modified; more styles can be easily added if necessary.
